Task:
Standard input consists of a single non-empty line of text.

Write a python script named swap-first-and-last.py which writes 
that text to standard putput with its first and last characters 
swapped.

Solution:

#!/usr/bin/env python3

s = input()
t = ""

while i < len(s):
  x = s[0]
  y = s[1:(len(s) - 1)]
  z = s[len(s) - 1]
  t = z + y + x
  i = i + 1

print(t)
